extendedInfo.description: Jeppesen Marine has developed the ultimate navigation and planning tool for todayâs âmobileâ society. From passionate, experienced boaters to casual travelers, Plan2Nav helps you receive more enjoyment from your time on the water, everywhere around the world. Are you ready to map? Our exclusive free app includes outstanding worldwide background charts, so you can start planning your journey right away! Plan your next cruise, set routes, look for marinas along your voyage or even share the tracks of your last adventureâ¦these are just some of the things you can do with Plan2Nav. Advanced navigation features Like a âhandheld chartplotter,â Plan 2Nav lets you: -View charts in âbirds eyeâ Perspective View -Enable GPS to track Speed Over Ground (SOG), Course Over Ground (COG) and Estimated Time of Arrival (ETA).* -Create and edit routes -View GPS tracks -Download free weather for a five-day forecast overlaid onto the chart -Select North Up or Course Up orientation for a fully rotating vector visualization -View Clock, Compass and set Distance Units Complete the Journey - Upgrade to full C-MAP by Jeppesen cartography Purchase affordable, expansive map coverage to unlock the full potential of Plan2Nav. Benefit from the features and award-winning technology that have made C-MAP by Jeppesen the choice of more than 1 million boaters worldwide: -NavAids -Detailed Harbor Charts -Exclusive Aerial Photos and Diagrams -C-Marina Ports Database -Dynamic Tides and Current Predictions -Depth Contours and Land Elevations Once downloaded, these feature-packed maps stay recorded on the device and are always accessible â even when no wireless connection is available * Continued use of GPS running in background can reduce battery life

reviews.title: Needs a lot more work
reviews.comment: Shame that active captain put thier name behind this app as working. Lots of small issues that need sorting. On trying to view active captain data program shuts down. Zoom not easy to work. There is a long list of issues in reviews. Once I  see a lot more 5 star reviews I will purchase.
reviews.author: Emma fiveflipflops

reviews.comment: Update - was a trial to get all running but is a nice product once it works\tI finally got everything running.  I think one problem is that I am used to the instant gratification of buying something and being able to install instantly.  With Jeppesen, it seems like their email confirmations, etc, take a 24 hour or so period to get issued to verify your status.  For the number of copies sold, you would think this would be faster.  but i do like it!  Program installed fine on my Galaxy s3 but doesn\'t seem to want to track to my GPS.  It took a couple of days to get the \'invite\' email to confirm my email, and then I went ahead and bought my local chart.  Can\'t figure out how to download that chart although it does say I now own it. Tech support is helpful but there is a 12-24 hour waiting list for responses.  I would dearly like to make this work to have the captain data available.  and, scarily enough, when you go to the website for technical support and look at the faq, it says that this software is ONLY available for IOS, so at the very least, they are not too excited about the android capabilities, and at the worst, the android announcement is premature?  I\'ll report back when and if I get this all working and perhaps increase my rating when and if!
reviews.author: stave kaimmer

reviews.title: phunsuch
reviews.comment: Could not register,   keep asking me to spell my email address correctly.  After 10 tries got frustrated and will uninstall
reviews.author: John Iscaro

reviews.title: Not good on my Nexus 7 (2013)
reviews.comment: Liked the idea of Active Captain integration, but performance is slow and features don\'t seem to work properly. If you try and zoom in, it over zooms and you lose your place. If you try to buy a chart, the outlines of the area being purchased don\'t show. There seems to be no way to keep North up while zooming.  Too bad.
reviews.author: John Howell

reviews.title: Has potential
reviews.comment: Zooming is horribly broken and without that, activecaptain data is unavailable.
reviews.author: Bob Damiano

reviews.title: Great interface, and chart representation
reviews.comment: This app would be perfect if the tidal current data had the ability to change the date for planning - like the tide height can. Have to use navionics for this.
reviews.author: stuart anderson

reviews.title: Some features need fixing Nexus 7
reviews.comment: Generally the app is pretty good, especially the charts.  There are a few things that need attention.  The one thing I dislike most about this app is that while touching  the screen to zoom or move, the screen reverts to the base map, so you can\'t see details or level of details. The compass doesn\'t work on Nexus 7 when stationary.  Cweather is brilliant, as is the support team at Jeppesen Marine.
reviews.author: Jim Thom

reviews.title: Getting there
reviews.comment: I have used Navionics but it doesn\'t have following functions that is included in Jeppesen\'s Plan2Nav: Course-Up rotation and Bird view. Map colors and fonts are not that good as in Navionics but you can live with those. If I have to choose I will say that Jeppesen is much better than Navionics because they have included those two killer features that are missing in Navionics software.  I gave 4 star for Plan2Nav and I\'m currently using it at Baltic Sea (Finland).
reviews.author: Tomi Sajaniemi

reviews.title: Needs to be better
reviews.comment: Maps look good, but unable to work out how to get the height of tide for my current time and some point in the future. Also not able to get the time of low water or high water for the current day.  The popup box shows the heights for low and high water, the graph of tidal heights looks nice but cannot interact with it. This part of the software is not as well designed as Navionics. Frustrated customer as the product promises a lot but user interface is clunky.
reviews.author: Chris Forker

reviews.title: Very twitchie program
reviews.comment: You do want a reliable program for navigation, but this one will get you in the ballpark (of it opens correctly). In Mexico, be very carefully inshore. Good for general navigation and much lower power drain than laptop. Loaded on nexus 7  & IPhone 4
reviews.author: Donald Murvine

reviews.comment: Works better on my galaxy SIII than on nexus7.  Needs a screen lock on nexus and could use a better menu on both devices.  Like how it shows tide directlion, but wish there were more details.  It has trouble acquiring satellites on nexus 7 after about a month of use. No updates fix this. Always end up rebooting.  Always have to hit GPS button to center map on your current location, unless you are underway, then its hard to search other parts of map.  The UK and Western European coast charts are great value for money.  Again viewing and searching the charts works better on smart phone than tablet.
reviews.author: Michael Wesselman

reviews.title: Not convinced
reviews.comment: I\'m not convinced the app is very user friendly...the navigation tools popping up in the way of the charts while looking at weather is not very good.  I did not bother to buy a map, it should come with a tutorial and a hi defintion example area to explore or something... I deleted after 30 seconds of use...
reviews.author: Mark Aylward

reviews.title: Pantech element
reviews.comment: The application doesn\'t display properly on the Element.  Its zoomed in and looks to be maybe 250x350 pixels.  Haven\'t had this issue with any other apps.
reviews.author: matt johnson

reviews.title: Jeppesen Support - Thank you!
reviews.comment: Jeppesen Marine customer support would like to thank everyone for taking time to comment, your feedback is important and appreciated. Plan2Nav Android is designed to use a proprietary web store compliant with Google policies and Jeppesen Marine is part of the Boeing company, it is a trusted international enterprise and its goal with its own web store is to better serve the particular needs of the distribution of maps and other services that will come. Web Store registration is done within Plan2Nav and requi
reviews.author: Jeppesen Marine

reviews.title: Very user friendly
reviews.comment: A great app with lot\'s of user friendly tools. If you own a boat you will want to take this with you on the water. Purchase the map or maps that suit your plans and plot away. Installed on my Samsung Galaxy 10.1 model 8013 tablet. However I think you get more bang for your buck with Navionics. While the app. from Jeppeson is free the maps are far more expensive and leave so many bodies of water not covered unlike Navionics with everything included for $30.00. I have both now but I can see that Navionics is the best bargain. I hope Jeppeson follows Navionics and offers an all in one purchase and covers more lakes and rivers in their package.
reviews.author: Richard Smith

reviews.title: Good try but barely usable
reviews.comment: I now have been playing around with this app for a long while and came to the conclusion that it\'s vastly inferior to the Navionics app. Don\'t waste your money on it, as I did. I will uninstall it as it squats on valuable memory space.
reviews.author: A Google User

reviews.title: APK loading on incomptible devices
reviews.comment: although Google play does not allow this app to be downloaded to so called \"incompatible devices\" it may run perfectly on them; therefore 5 stars! Reason for incompatibility not found (manufacturer / model / region / language / location service / GPS ???)  Rooting was needed to download the APK (other trick later discovered: APK downloader). Plan2Nav installed fine on chinese iFive-MX tablet, registered and downloaded detailed maps. Testing oke thus will buy the needed charts.
reviews.author: Piet Knoop
